.TH "drm_syncobj_get_handle" 9 "drm_syncobj_get_handle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_syncobj_get_handle \- get a handle from a syncobj
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_syncobj_get_handle
.BI "(struct drm_file *file_private "  ","
.BI "struct drm_syncobj *syncobj "  ","
.BI "u32 *handle "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file_private" 12
drm file private pointer
.IP "syncobj" 12
Sync object to export
.IP "handle" 12
out parameter with the new handle
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Exports a sync object created with \fBdrm_syncobj_create\fP as a handle on
\fIfile_private\fP to userspace.

Returns 0 on success or a negative error value on failure.
